Job Description Xe is seeking an experienced Product Manager to join our Product Management team. Reporting to the Director, Product Management, you will be involved in developing strategy to expand, maintain and enhance Xe’s premium products and services. You will join a dynamic and fast-paced environment and work with cross-functional teams to define the vision, strategy and roadmap for our Currency Data Feed product.

Responsibilities include overseeing the creation of product requirements documents, schedules and supporting materials in partnership with design, marketing, technology, accounting and data teams. The Product Manager provides day-to-day cross-functional leadership to ensure the timely delivery of projects which meet established feature, usability, content and quality requirements.

The successful candidate should thrive in a fast-paced, collaborative environment and be able to adapt and adjust plans on-the-fly. The position requires interaction with a wide variety of internal stakeholders at various levels of the organization. Candidates must possess the ability and willingness to balance customer needs with business priorities and articulate the rationale behind decisions. They must also have exceptional project management skills.

If you’re passionate about Product Management, exceptional at creating meaningful business relationships, and love crafting and implementing innovative ideas, then we’re glad you’re here.


Responsibilities

Gain a deep understanding of Xe’s Currency Data Product and its user base

Learn, refine, enhance, and maintain the vision and strategy for the Xe currency data product line;

Work closely with cross functional teams (e.g. Software Development, Quality Assurance, Marketing, IT, Customer Support, Accounting) to support the achievement of your goals;

Liaise with various department leads to define project scope, time lines, and to allocate relevant resources;

Manage the Salesforces administration and reporting for the Xe Currency Data Feed Product

Perform market research to determine customer needs, opportunities and understand the target market;

Identify and define potential new products and enhancements to existing products that will better meet customer needs and reach new customers;

Establish and cultivate relationships with key partners and suppliers;

Build and present business cases to the senior leadership teams;

Participate in creating, implementing and maintaining Xe’s Onboarding/Offboarding Process, including but not limited to enhanced methods of customer communication, client satisfaction surveys etc.;

Participate in creating, implementing and maintaining Xe’s Vendor Referral Program which includes actively researching and building integration practices with Development Solution providers;

Establish cross selling opportunities with the various Euronet Business entities.


Requirements

Bachelor’s degree or demonstrable equivalent professional experience;

Minimum 3 – 5 years of Product Management experience;

Previous Product Management experience with APIs and SaaS products would be considered an asset

Solution oriented, highly-motivated and proactive self-starter

Experience and/or working knowledge of Salesforce and Adobe Analytics would be considered an asset

Experience in an Agile environment would be considered an asset;

Confluence / Jira experience would be considered an asset;

Strong customer service/client relationship skills to identify and maintain third party integration opportunities;

Exceptional analytical, problem solving and research skills;

Excellent written and verbal communication and presentation skills.

Outstanding organizational skills and the ability to balance multiple priorities

