Marketing Coordinator, Multimedia Design
Vancouver, Canada

At Avigilon we are helping solve some of the biggest challenges around safety and physical security by developing advanced artificial intelligence (AI) technologies and products that are used to help keep people, businesses, and cities around the world safer. Avigilon, a Motorola Solutions company, designs, develops, and manufactures advanced AI, video analytics, network video management software and hardware, surveillance cameras, and access control solutions that help change the way people interact with their security systems.
Founded in 2004 in Vancouver, Avigilon has been a driving force behind the security industry’s AI evolution and has continuously been a company that stands for innovation and growth. At Avigilon, you will find a culture of thought-leaders who are passionate about creating exciting new solutions for security and surveillance. We seek problem-solvers who are eager to rise to the challenges of a continuously evolving technological industry, and those who want to make an impact of the safety of people and businesses globally.
We believe that diversity spawns innovation – the more diverse our employees are, the more ideas and talents we have to excel as a leader in the technology sector. If you would like to be part of a dynamic team of people who are ambitious, focused, and hardworking then we look forward to meeting you!

Responsibilities include:

Create/update print marketing materials including promotional flyers, brochures and guides, print ads, case studies and whitepapers, display banners and posters;
Create/update digital marketing assets including digital/social media ads, event and tradeshow invitations, Google Slides presentations, multimedia animations, and custom infographics;
Collaborate with internal stakeholders including Product Marketing, Regional Marketing, Event Management, and Communications teams for source content, and the Localization team for translated versions of final materials
Respond to requests for logos, high-resolution photos, and custom graphics for websites, news releases, social media, email newsletters, and Google Slides presentations—in particular, ensuring all presentations meet brand standards for compliance, consistency, and quality;
Manage multiple project timelines, approval processes, deadlines, and stakeholder expectations;
Develop/maintain well-organized templates, shared assets, source files, and project tracking;
Actively participate in team meetings/conference calls, inform managers on project status, ask for assistance/approval when required, and support other Marketing Team members;
Stay current on features and changes in the software environments you work with on a regular basis.
Qualifications:

Highly skilled and experienced with Adobe Creative Cloud software:
including at least Photoshop, Illustrator, InDesign, Acrobat, and a working understanding of shared assets, templates, and style libraries,
with Bridge and/or Animate knowledge preferred;
Experience with G Suite Apps—at minimum Gmail, Drive, Slides, Docs, and Sheets
Proficient in design fundamentals including page layout, vector graphics, photo correction (photography experience a plus), image optimization for multiple mediums, and corporate brand standard compliance;
Proficient in preparing files for print production, email distribution, and digital/web use with embedded links, cross-references, fillable forms, and other interactivity
Comfortable with communication—including presenting work—in-person, via phone, email, Google Chat, and Google Meet conference calls;
Excellent organization and time management skills, including the ability to efficiently prioritize multiple projects with short turnaround times;
Commitment to striving for the Marketing Creative Team’s exceptionally high standards for design quality, attention to detail, and meeting fast-paced, yet reasonable deadlines;
Confidence in taking ownership of assigned projects and being dedicated to their success;
Ambition to think outside the box—while keeping one hand firmly attached to it—challenging both yourself and your teammates; and
Knowledgeable on latest digital/social marketing trends, best practices, and innovations to make confident strategy recommendations.

Perks and Benefits:

As a full-time employee at Avigilon, you are eligible to receive a comprehensive benefits package which includes MSP, extended health, dental, medical insurance while travelling You will also receive a health spending account to cover additional healthcare costs, such as vision care, RMT and chiropractor visits.
